# Quick Notes Taker  
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  
This Batch File script allows users to **add and save notes** easily into a text file.  
Each note entered will be appended to a file called `notes.txt` with a timestamp.  
This is useful for **quickly jotting down thoughts, reminders, or ideas**.  
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  

# STEPS  
1. Open Notepad  
2. Copy and Paste the Following Code  
3. Save the File as a Batch File (`notes_taker.bat`)  
4. Run `notes_taker.bat`  
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  

# CODE  
@echo off  
title Quick Notes Taker  
cls  

echo ===================================  
echo        QUICK NOTES TAKER  
echo ===================================  

:: Ask for a note from the user  
set /p note=Enter your note:  

:: Append the note to notes.txt with a timestamp  
echo [%date% %time%] %note% >> notes.txt  

echo Note saved successfully!  
echo ===================================  
pause  
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  

# Usage Tips  
1. Run `notes_taker.bat`.  
2. Enter your note and press **Enter**.  
3. The note will be saved in `notes.txt` with a **date and time** stamp.  
4. Open `notes.txt` anytime to view all saved notes.  
5. Press any key to exit.  

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
